 security over subsistence agriculture, development over sustainability, market participation over social welfare, and ideologies of self-care over public health. Trade agreements negotiated to improve lives have resulted in unintended consequences for people’s everyday lives.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aAgriculture and statezMexico. 0aFood industry and tradezMexico. 0aFree tradexEconomic aspectszMexico. 0aFree tradexHealth aspectszMexico. 0aFree tradexSocial aspectszMexico. 0aNutritionally induced diseaseszMexico. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Anthropology / Cultural & Social.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Complete eBook-Package 2018z978311066767740uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9780520965447?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520965447423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520965447/original  a978-3-11-066767-7  University of California Press Complete eBook-Package 2018b2018  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles